{
  "stem": "18865.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 584.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "When I came to America and I tried to speak American English, it was even worse.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My-- they also went to school to learn English.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And other than that, he-- nobody was allowed to work.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, my parents had sent a lift, which is a huge box, like as big as a room, with furniture, one to England, and one to America.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we-- when the war started, we were told now all the numbers of the people who are still in Germany are exhausted, are finished.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They will never be called, which means that every quota number outside of Germany had moved forward.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was a terrible thought, that we are taking over for those who were not able to go.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But for-- for-- for us, it was fortunate.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But I never forgot the fact that the numbers that we were given, that we were able to leave and go to America while the people who couldn't were probably killed.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Very hard to accept.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh my goodness, yes.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Dozens and dozens and dozens.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It kept-- I didn't even go anymore, because when I was on the farm, they had ditches.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we didn't have air raid shelters there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we had to go-- we all had boots.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we had to go into these wet ditches.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I realized that the best time for me to write my diary was when they all went into the ditches.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I stayed in the house.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I didn't even go anymore.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was one after the other.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the news got worse and worse and worse.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And-- and I tried, at one time after the war started, they said that the Red Cross was helping to get some Jews out, especially young people.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
